# Java SOP

- Match project formatter (Google / Sun / team); run before commit.
- Prefer immutable value types; null-safety per project (`Optional`, annotations).
- Layering per repo (Spring, modules); no god classes or circular deps.
- Exceptions: checked vs unchecked consistent with codebase; never swallow without log.
- Records for DTOs when JDK 17+ and team agrees; Lombok only if repo already uses it.
- Resources: try-with-resources; close streams and connections explicitly in legacy code.
- Tests: JUnit 5; unit vs integration packages separated (`src/test/java/...`).
- Build: Maven or Gradle as declared — do not mix without approval.
- Secrets via env, vault, or Spring config — never commit credentials or keystores.
